<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Dart2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Dart,</orth> vb. tr. to throw, to shoot: <cit><quote>thine eye --s forth the fire that burneth me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 196" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 196</bibl></cit>. <emph>which</emph> (eye) <cit><quote>after him she --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 196" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 196</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. son 139.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 139, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.396" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 396</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.25" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 5, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.137" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. V, 2, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 14</bibl>. <cit><quote>all curses . . . be --ed on thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.314" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 314</bibl></cit>. <emph>where 'twill not extend, thither he --s it</emph> (viz his sword) <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 112</bibl>. <cit><quote>d. your flames into her eyes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 167</bibl></cit>. -- Absolutely: <cit><quote>--ing Parthia,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 1, 1</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>